The paper discusses designing reward functions for robot planning and reinforcement learning, which falls under the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments conducted involve motion planning for a manipulator, which is a common topic in robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses user studies to measure effort and solution quality, which suggests a focus on machine learning and optimization (cs.LG). The divide-and-conquer approach presented in the paper is a form of system design, which could fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the user studies involve measuring user effort and solution quality, which suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
